    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's complicated, but isn't the \"state collapse\" part the main thing people point to when they say it was a failure? like, if the goal was stability in the region, it clearly didn't work. isn't it more accurate to call it a strategic failure even if it helped people in the short term?",
