      "content": "that makes sense. so if we look at it through that lens, it kind of feels like the humanitarian argument was just used to justify a policy that ended up being a disaster for long-term security. do you think there's actually any legitimate geopolitical argument for why it could be considered a success, or is it mostly just about the moral aspect?",
